  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2025-04-02",
    "date": "2026-05-05T21:43:39Z",
    "text": "Aviation Medication Transparency Act of 2025\n\nThis bill directs the Federal Aviation Administration (FAA) to compile, publish, and annually update a list of medications that may be safely prescribed to pilots and air traffic controllers for the purposes of issuing a medical certification. The list must be publicly available on the FAA website and distributed to those seeking a license and medical\u00a0certification.\n\nCurrently, the FAA does not have a list of approved medications. However, the FAA does have lists for Aviation Medical Examiners of Do Not Issue medications and Do Not Fly medications."
  },
